Album Notes
Personnel: Francisco Javier Ramirez Lopez (keyboards); Felipe Gutierrez Robledo, Jose De Jesus De Loza Guevara, Jolanta Michalewicz Brucz, Mariana Martinez Cruz, Victor Padilla Zaragoza.

Arranger: Pedro Ramirez.

The audio companion to the deluxe DVD concert of the same name (both of which were released in 2008), PRIMERA FILA presents Mexican pop icon Vicente Fernandez in all his legendary glory. Since his emergence in the 1960s, Fernandez has been the keeper of Mexico's ranchera tradition, and his popularity in his native country, the U.S., and abroad has elevated him to superstar status. With stirring, passionate performances from Fernandez and his seasoned band, not to mention classics such as "El Rey," "No Vuelvo a Amar," and "Amor Mio," PRIMERA FILA shows why.
